
A Berkeley DB stores data as key/value pairs. Data is later retrieved by their key.

{ Supported formats

  Berkeley DB supports the following file formats (or *access methods*):
    • BTree (Sorted balanced tree structure)
    • Hash (extensible dynamic hashing scheme)
    • Heap
    • Queue (fast access to fixed-length records, accessed either sequentially or by logical record number)
    • Recno (fixed- and variable-length records, accessed either sequentially or by logical record number, optionally backed by a flat text file)

}
